%I A393584 #52 Mar 28 2026 13:09:58
%S A393584 1,1,2,2,3,3,3,4,4,5,5,5,6,6,6,7,7,8,8,8,9,9,10,10,10,11,11,11,12,12,
%T A393584 13,13,13
%N A393584 a(n) is the minimum, over all partitions {X, Y} of {1..2n} with |X| = |Y|, of the maximum number of pairs (x, y) with the same difference x - y for x in X and y in Y.
%C A393584 a(n) is floor(5*n/13) for small n but a(n) ~ (c - o(1))*n for some 0.379005 < c < 0.380876. - _Sharvil Kesarwani_, Mar 04 2026
%C A393584 From _Bert Dobbelaere_, Mar 02 2026: (Start)
%C A393584 a(k*n) <= k*a(n) can be shown by constructing a set X' containing all elements in range [k*(x-1)+1...k*x] for each element x of X (similar for Y).
%C A393584 a(n+1) <= a(n) + 1 can be shown by extending X with element 2n+1 and Y with element 2n+2.
%C A393584 It follows that a(n)/n >= the lower bound for c, otherwise it would be violated for arbitrary large k. (End)
%H A393584 Thomas F. Bloom, <a href="https://www.erdosproblems.com/36">Erdős Problem #36</a>
%F A393584 a(2n) <= n.
%F A393584 a(k*n) <= k * a(n) for positive integer k. - _Bert Dobbelaere_, Mar 02 2026
%F A393584 a(n+1) <= a(n) + 1. - _Bert Dobbelaere_, Mar 02 2026
%e A393584 For n = 2, the equal partitions of {1,2,3,4} are:
%e A393584 - {1,2} and {3,4}: the differences are 2, 1, 3, 2: max repetition is 2.
%e A393584 - {1,3} and {2,4}: the differences are 1, -1, 3, 1, max repetition is 2.
%e A393584 - {1,4} and {2,3}: the differences are 1, -2, 2, -1, max repetition is 1.
%e A393584 Hence a(2) = 1.
%e A393584 For n = 3, the partition {1,2,4} and {3,5,6} has at most two pairs with the same difference, so a(3) <= 2. Exhaustive checking shows that no partition has lower repetition.
%o A393584 (Python)
%o A393584 from itertools import combinations
%o A393584 from collections import Counter
%o A393584 def a(n): return min(max(Counter(a-b for a in A for b in range(1, 2 * n + 1) if b not in A).values()) for A in combinations(range(1, 2*n + 1),n))
%K A393584 nonn,more
%O A393584 1,3
%A A393584 _Touch Sungkawichai_, Feb 22 2026
